texts.value: Serine protease that hydrolyzes the inactive zymogen hepatocyte growth factor (HGFsc) to an activated disulfide-linked heterodimer, then initiating hepatocyte growth factor receptor signaling pathway
Heterodimer of a short chain and a long chain linked by a disulfide bond
Exists as an inactive zymogen in plasma (PubMed:8226803). Exists as an active heterodimeric form in serum (PubMed:7683665)
The active form of HGFAC presents in the serum is derived from the COOH-terminal region of the precursor by the cleavage of bonds between Arg-372 and Val-373 and Arg-407 and Ile-408
Belongs to the peptidase S1 family
It is uncertain whether Met-1 is the initiator
